{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id56c07b27-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2307"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2307"},"text":"§ 2307.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Retirement of enlisted members: increase in retired pay","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"An enlisted member voluntarily or involuntarily retired after twenty years of service who was cited for extraordinary heroism in the line of duty shall be entitled to an increase in retired pay. The retired pay shall be increased by 10 percent of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id56c07b28-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2307/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the active-duty pay and permanent additions thereto of the grade or rating with which retired when the member’s retired pay is computed under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s2504/a"},"text":"section 2504(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":"; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id56c07b29-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s2307/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the member’s retired pay base under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1407"},"text":"section 1407 of title 10","children":[],"tail":", when a member’s retired pay is computed under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s2504/b"},"text":"section 2504(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id56c07b2a-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393"},"text":"Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/521"},"text":"63 Stat. 521","children":[],"tail":", § 357; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-08-03/ch536/s17"},"text":"Aug. 3, 1950, ch. 536, § 17","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/407"},"text":"64 Stat. 407","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/114/s1/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–114, § 1(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-09-06"},"text":"Sept. 6, 1963","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/77/144"},"text":"77 Stat. 144","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/557/s15/a/3/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–557, § 15(a)(3)(A)","children":[],"tail":", (B), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/2865"},"text":"98 Stat. 2865","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/348/tII/s205/b/9"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–348, title II, § 205(b)(9)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/700"},"text":"100 Stat. 700","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/241/s6"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–241, § 6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/2210"},"text":"105 Stat. 2210","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/120/tII/s215/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–120, title II, § 215(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b)(1), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-02-08"},"text":"Feb. 8, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/45"},"text":"130 Stat. 45","children":[],"tail":", 46; renumbered § 2307 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282/tI"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282, title I","children":[],"tail":", §§ 113(b), 123(b)(2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-12-04"},"text":"Dec. 4, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/4221"},"text":"132 Stat. 4221","children":[],"tail":", 4240.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id56c07b2b-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id56c07b2c-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 14, U.S.C., 1946 ed., §§ 185, 185d (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1939-05-24/ch146"},"text":"May 24, 1939, ch. 146","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1, 5, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/53/755"},"text":"53 Stat. 755","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (b) is new and implements the preceding subsection; it seems necessary in view of certain statutes enacted as the result of World War II.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (c) is based on title 14, U.S.C., 1946 ed., § 185d (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1939-05-24/ch146/s5"},"text":"May 24, 1939, ch. 146, § 5","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/53/756"},"text":"53 Stat. 756","children":[],"tail":"). Said section has been divided. The first sentence is incorporated in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s423"},"text":"section 423 of this title","children":[],"tail":". The second proviso is incorporated in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s424"},"text":"section 424 of this title","children":[],"tail":". The remainder is placed in this subsection."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Changes were made in phraseology. 81st Congress, House Report No. 557.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id56c07b2d-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id56c07b2e-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282/s113/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282, § 113(b)","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s357"},"text":"section 357 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282/s123/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282, § 123(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 2504(a)” for “section 423(a)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282/s123/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282, § 123(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 2504(b)” for “section 423(b)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2016—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/120/s215/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–120, § 215(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Retirement of enlisted members: increase in retired pay” for “Involuntary retirement of enlisted members” in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/120/s215/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–120, § 215(a)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (i) designation before “An enlisted member” and struck out subsecs. (a) to (h) and (j) which related to procedures and requirements for involuntary retirement of enlisted members."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1991—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/241"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–241","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Involuntary retirement of enlisted members” for “Enlisted Personnel Board” in section catchline and amended text generally. Prior to amendment, text provided that the Commandant assemble annually a Coast Guard Enlisted Personnel Board to recommend enlisted members for retirement, that the recommendations be transmitted to the Commandant for approval, in which event the enlisted members concerned would be notified and given opportunity to file a written protest, which would require a subsequent annual Board determination and approval by the Commandant to effect the involuntary retirement of that member, and further provided that an enlisted member with twenty years’ service retired from active duty by the Commandant pursuant to this section was to receive retired pay, and that an enlisted member voluntarily or involuntarily retired by reason of twenty years’ service who had been cited for extraordinary heroism was entitled to an increase in retired pay."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/348/s205/b/9/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–348, § 205(b)(9)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “retired pay” for “the retired pay of the grade or rating with which retired”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/348/s205/b/9/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–348, § 205(b)(9)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted provision that retired pay be increased by an amount equal to 10 percent of the active-duty pay and permanent additions thereto of the grade or rating with which retired, in the case of a member whose retired pay is computed under 423(a) of this title, or the member’s retired pay base under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s1407"},"text":"section 1407 of title 10","children":[],"tail":", in the case of a member whose retired pay is computed under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s423/b"},"text":"section 423(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":" for provision that the retired pay be increased by an amount equal to 10 per cent of the active-duty pay and permanent additions thereto of the grade or rating with which retired."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/557/s15/a/3/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–557, § 15(a)(3)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted reference to enlisted member for reference to enlisted man wherever appearing in subsecs. (a) to (c)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/557/s15/a/3/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–557, § 15(a)(3)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted reference to enlisted members for reference to enlisted men in two places."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1963—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/114"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–114","children":[],"tail":" struck out provisions which entitled enlisted men whose average marks in conduct were not less than 97½ percent of the maximum to a 10-percent increase of their retired pay."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1950—Subsec. (c). Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-08-03"},"text":"Aug. 3, 1950","children":[],"tail":", substituted “years’ ” for “years”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id56c07b2f-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id56c07b30-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Enlisted Men in Service on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-09-06"},"text":"September 6, 1963","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/114/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–114, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-09-06"},"text":"Sept. 6, 1963","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/77/144"},"text":"77 Stat. 144","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/88/114/s2"},"text":"“The amendment made by subsection (1) of section 1 of this Act [amending this section] does not apply to any enlisted man in service on the effective date of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-09-06"},"text":"Sept. 6, 1963","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id56c07b31-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Service Credit for Certain Enlisted Personnel","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-03/ch394"},"text":"Act June 3, 1948, ch. 394","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/302"},"text":"62 Stat. 302","children":[],"tail":", provided for special service credit for enlisted men of the Coast Guard who, in 1940 and 1941, were discharged to accept employment as policemen and guards at the Ivigtut Cryolite Mine, Greenland, and who reenlisted in the Coast Guard within three months after the termination of their service at the mine."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
